# =============================================================================
# CE-OS environment variables — copy to `.env.local` for local development.
# =============================================================================
#
# Vite exposes ONLY variables prefixed with `VITE_` to browser code via
# `import.meta.env`. Anything without that prefix is NOT exposed to the client
# unless you explicitly inject it (e.g. `vite.config.ts` `define`).
#
# Classification:
#   SAFE   — OK to ship to the browser (public IDs, publishable keys, URLs).
#   DANGEROUS — Must never be bundled into the client; use server / Edge proxy.
#
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Gemini / Google AI (care notes draft on Cultivars page)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DANGEROUS — API keys authenticate billing-backed APIs and must NOT be
# client-exposed. Current code reads `import.meta.env.VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY` in
# `src/pages/Cultivars.tsx`, which bundles the value into the production JS.
#
# Recommended: proxy generation through `/api/...` (Vercel serverless) or a
# Supabase Edge Function; keep the real key in `GEMINI_API_KEY` (no VITE_) on
# the server only. Do NOT add a VITE_-prefixed secret copy.
#
# VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY="<redacted>"   # DANGEROUS if set — exposed in client bundle
# GEMINI_API_KEY="<redacted>"        # Server/build only — see vite.config `define`

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Vite build / dev (automatic — usually no .env entry needed)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# import.meta.env.DEV / MODE / PROD — SAFE (build-time flags; see Vite docs).

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional local tooling (not used in `src/` today; vite.config.ts references)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DISABLE_HMR=true                 # SAFE — dev server only; disables HMR when set.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase Auth (magic link) — wired in src/lib/auth.ts, Login, RequireAuth
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SAFE — public project URL and anon key (RLS must protect data once tables exist)
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL="https://xxxx.supabase.co"
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="<your-anon-key>"
# Comma-separated emails allowed to use CE-OS after Supabase signs them in (single-operator gate)
# VITE_CE_OS_OPERATOR_EMAILS="operator@example.com"

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Future public client config (placeholders — not wired in src yet)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Example patterns when you add integrations:
# VITE_SHOPIFY_STOREFRONT_URL="https://your-store.myshopify.com" # SAFE — public storefront URL
# VITE_SHOPIFY_STOREFRONT_URL="https://your-store.myshopify.com" # SAFE — public storefront URL
# VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY="pk_live_..."                   # SAFE — publishable key only

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Never put these in VITE_ vars or client code
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY — DANGEROUS — bypasses RLS; server-only.
# SHOPIFY_ADMIN_API_TOKEN — DANGEROUS — admin API access.
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY — DANGEROUS — payment secret.
# OPENAI_API_KEY / ANTHROPIC_API_KEY — DANGEROUS — billing-backed LLM keys.
